The paper deals with the problem of entity retrieval for long concept queries, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes novel techniques to improve the precision and recall of entity retrieval for long concept queries. This problem is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on IR and NLP, cs.IR and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DB, cs.CL, and cs.LG.
